div.p:
Let ABC be the given circle, and DEF the given triangle;
             thus it is required to inscribe in the circle ABC a triangle equiangular
             with the triangle DEF .

Let ABC be the given circle, and DEF the given triangle;
                thus it is required to circumscribe about the circle ABC a
             triangle equiangular with the triangle DEF .

For, since the straight line BD is a diameter of the circle
               ABCD , therefore BAD is a semicircle; 
               therefore the angle BAD is right. [ III. 31 ]
